summary: An email from an Assistant United States Attorney in the Southern District of New York to FBI and NYPD contacts, requesting follow-up information related to a 2019 interview. The email asks for photos referenced in an attached FBI 302 form and seeks confirmation of a subject's place of birth and citizenship, believed to be the UK.

events.title: Interview referenced in FBI 302
events.description: An interview was conducted, documented in an FBI 302 report. The email references an attached PDF of this 302 and requests photos that were part of the investigation file.

locations: United States Attorney's Office Southern District of New York, One St. Andrew's Plaza, New York, New York 10007
UK (referenced as suspected place of birth and citizenship)
keyFacts: An AUSA from the SDNY is actively following up on investigative details from a 2019 interview in August 2021.
The follow-up request is for photographs referenced in an FBI 302 report and confirmation of a subject's birthplace and citizenship.
The communication demonstrates ongoing inter-agency coordination (between USAO, FBI, and NYPD) on the case years after the initial interview.
